        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Hugh McGuffln to Austin, August 18, 1824.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Natchitoches </placeName><date when="1824-08-18">18th August 1824</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>I should have visited your Country ere this only on account of
<persName>Mrs. McGuffin</persName> going to the <placeName>warm Springs</placeName> She will return about
the <date when="1824-09-15">fifteenth of Sept.</date> Shortly after which I will set out for that
place there is nothing worthy of Communicating to you now the
Mule that your <persName>Brother </persName>left with me I Delivered to his order about
two weeks ago the Horse is not here at present but I think he will
[be] in a short time when I go on there I will bring him with me.&#8212;</p>

<p>Adue untill I see you</p>

<p>Write me if you have any oportunity</p>

<p><persName>H. McGuffin</persName>.</p>

<p>P. S.   I send your <persName>Muscetoe Barr</persName> by <persName>Mr. House</persName> that you left at
<placeName><persName>Mr. Jas. Denny</persName>s</placeName> also your Spanish Dictionary   <persName>H. McG</persName>.</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Coln. S. F. Austin</persName>&#8212;<placeName>Brazos</placeName>&#8212;Per <persName>Mr. House</persName>.</p>

        </div1>
